Eric Hwang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"subtasks":[],"customfield_12310291":null,"reporter":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ehwang","name":"ehwang","key":"ehwang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Eric Hwang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"customfield_12310290":null,"aggregateprogress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"customfield_12311024":null,"environment":null,"customfield_12313520":null,"customfield_12311020":null,"duedate":null,"customfield_12310250":null,"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"comment":{"comments":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12432494/comment/12740404","id":"12740404","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rsm","name":"rsm","key":"rsm","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Raghotham Murthy","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"As a work around, can you execute \"describe <tablename>\" to get the schema?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rsm","name":"rsm","key":"rsm","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Raghotham Murthy","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2009-08-07T05:08:48.420+0000","updated":"2009-08-07T05:08:48.420+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12432494/comment/12740407","id":"12740407","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ehwang","name":"ehwang","key":"ehwang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Eric Hwang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"That would work, but I was hoping to solve both this and JIRA-671 in one fell swoop. Don't we just need to determine whether the table has a partition, and then append the partition key onto the field schemas returned by the deserializer?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ehwang","name":"ehwang","key":"ehwang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Eric Hwang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2009-08-07T05:18:38.447+0000","updated":"2009-08-07T05:18:38.447+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12432494/comment/12740414","id":"12740414","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ehwang","name":"ehwang","key":"ehwang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Eric Hwang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Actually I just talked to Zheng offline and I guess the get_fields function should NOT return the partition column under its proper usage. I can work around this by calling get_tables and then join the partitionkey field descriptors with the result of get_fields. I'll do this for now, however, this seems rather roundabout and I think there should still be a function which just returns all field descriptors altogether.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ehwang","name":"ehwang","key":"ehwang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Eric Hwang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2009-08-07T05:33:43.136+0000","updated":"2009-08-07T05:33:43.136+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12432494/comment/12740425","id":"12740425","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rsm","name":"rsm","key":"rsm","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Raghotham Murthy","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"bq.  I think there should still be a function which just returns all field descriptors altogether.\n\nThat makes sense. Instead of writing a work around, why not just add a function to the metastore thrift api that returns all columns (including partition columns)?\n{code}\nlist<FieldSchema> get_schema(1:string db_name, 2:string tbl_name) \n         throws (1: MetaException o1, 2: UnknownTableException o2, 3: UnknownDBException o3),\n{code}","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rsm","name":"rsm","key":"rsm","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Raghotham Murthy","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2009-08-07T06:36:47.935+0000","updated":"2009-08-07T06:36:47.935+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12432494/comment/12740765","id":"12740765","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ehwang","name":"ehwang","key":"ehwang","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Eric Hwang","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Sounds like a good idea. I'll do that instead. Does anyone know if thrift permits the overloading of function names? The Hive server already has a function called get_schema with different arguments.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=ehwang","